This paper discusses the use of social media tools in scholarly communication and explores the properties of altmetrics. It focuses on the impact of articles published by the Public Library of Science, which is a digital library that covers various fields including computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries). Additionally, the paper discusses topics related to social media, information retrieval, and data analysis, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
